---
// Scene 4: Transfer — The recipe that transfers
// amplitude ∝ 1/lens-strength
---

<section id="transfer" class="section-divider">
  <div class="prose-section">
    <h2>The recipe that transfers: geometry doesn't, method does</h2>

    <p class="text-lg">
      Steering a Nemotron-Mini-4B works great with a registered recipe: entropy gating, amplitude
      α=0.1, write site at layer 20, etc. The question: does it work on a different model?
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg">
      <strong>Direct transfer (naive):</strong> Copy the exact recipe to Qwen3-4B, unmodified.
      <em>Result: fails flat. Lift +0.05, nowhere near the 0.2 threshold.</em>
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg">
      <strong>Why?</strong> Qwen3's band-exit Jacobians are ~10× weaker in transport strength
      (max‖J‖/√d) than Nemotron's. The geometry doesn't transfer. But the method does.
    </p>

    <div class="my-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-warning/10 to-success/10 border border-warning/50 rounded-lg p-8">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl mb-6">The calibration recipe</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Step 1: Probe</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Run a small dose-response scan on the target model to find candidate write sites
            and measure the Jacobian transport strength at each site.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Step 2: Scale</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Compute <code>α_target = α_source × (J_source / J_target)</code>.
            <br />
            <strong>The rule:</strong> amplitude ∝ 1/lens-strength.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Step 3: Steer</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Run the full protocol (entropy gating, τ from the target's baseline,
            readback verify) with the scaled amplitude on the target's calibrated site.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-sm mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Step 4: Confirm</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Verify within budget and above threshold (≥ 0.2 lift) on ≥3 independent seeds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg font-semibold">
      Result on Qwen3-4B (site 24, α=0.3, 3 independent seeds):
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-sm text-muted uppercase tracking-wide">Gated lift</div>
        <div class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-success">0.40</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">vs prefill 0.17</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-sm text-muted uppercase tracking-wide">Entropy cost</div>
        <div class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-success">−0.13</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Within ±0.5 nats budget</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-950 border-l-4 border-success p-6 rounded">
      <p class="font-semibold mb-2">The paper's one-line summary:</p>
      <p class="text-lg italic">
        "The method transfers; the geometry does not."
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-sm text-muted mt-8">
      <strong>Evidence:</strong> gate_L13_recipe (first calibrated transfer on Qwen3) ·
      gate_L14_multiseed (confirmed at 4 seeds, 0.33–0.48 lift, all above threshold)
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
